definition.value: A pyranone substituted with one or more halogen atoms.
A pyranone substituted with one or more bromine atoms.
A compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more halogen atoms
A compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more chlorine atoms
A chloroindole that is a compound based on an indole skeleton with a chlorine atom bonded to the nitrogen atom of the indole.
Glycoside compounds that have a 1-keto-8,9-dihydroxyanthracene skeleton, a functionalized alkyl chain at the 3- position, and two oligosaccharide chains of variable lengths.
An organobromine compound that is a compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more bromine atoms.
A class of several closely related glycosidic antibiotics obtained from Actinomyces (or Streptomyces) olivoreticuli.
A compound based on an indole skeleton with a bromine atom bonded to the nitrogen atom of the indole.
A fibre with a diameter of approximately 100 nm.
A titanium dioxide nanotube in which a small percentage of oxygen atoms have been replaced by nitrogen atoms.
A nanorod composed of zinc oxide.
A zinc oxide nanorod containing a small percentage of antimony atoms.
A nanoparticle consisting of a two metal elements.
A gold nanoparticle covered with a thin coat of palladium atoms.
A tryptophan derivative that is tryptophan substituted  by a methyl group at position 5 of the indole ring.
A nanocrystal composed of magnesium oxide.
Crystalline aggregates of atoms (100-10,000 atoms) with a diameter of approximately 10 nm.
A ribbon with nanometre width.
A sheet with nanometre thickness.
A compound consisting of a porphyrin ring bonded via one of its methine groups to a methylene group on a second porphyrin ring.
A porphyrin compound substituted at three of the four methine groups of the porphyrin ring.
A porphyrin compound substituted on opposing methine groups of the porphyrin ring.
A porphyrin compound containing a porphyrin ring with one double bond fewer than in porphyrin itself.
A porphyrin compound substituted with one or more formyl groups.
A porphyrin compound substituted with one or more formyl groups bonded to a pyrrole group of the porphyrin ring.
A compound which is a tautomer of porphyrin containing a saturated meso carbon atom.
A porphyrin compound substituted with one or more phenyl groups.
A glycolipid and which the glyco component is specified as galactosyl.
A compound containing three porphyrin rings.
A substituted porphyrin compound containing one or more chlorine atoms.
A cembrane diterpenoid obtained from tobacco and shown to have antitumour-promoting activity.
An antifungal metabolite of Sordaria araneosa that inhibits protein synthesis. It has a tetracyclic diterpene glycoside structure.
